- The core issue is that our Rust implementation uses `ls.linenumber` throughout the code generator, while C Lua uses `ls->lastline`, which trails one token behind
- This line number tracking problem is pervasive in the parser, though the real fix might be more targeted in how `emit_inst` and `cg_storevar` handle instruction emission

